<section xml:id='date-reference' xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
	<title>Date and Time Representation</title>
	<para>
	  &api_name; has many parameters and fields which use dates and times. This section summarises the representation of those parameters.
  </para>
  <section id='dates-times-reference'>
    <title>Dates/Times</title>
    <para>
      &api_name; allows very fine time resolutions, down to the minute. Dates/Times are represented in the standard IS0 8601<biblioref linkend="ISO8601"/> format:
    </para>
    <programlisting>YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssTZD</programlisting>
    <para>
      For example:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>2009-08-01T14:30:55Z (UTC)</listitem>
      <listitem>2009-08-01T14:30:55+00:00 (GMT)</listitem>
      <listitem>2009-08-01T14:30:55-08:00 (GMT-8) </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
  <section id='duration-reference'>
    <title>Durations</title>
    <para>
      Durations are also used in some paramters. These are also represented in IS0 8601<biblioref linkend="ISO8601"/> format:
    </para>
    <programlisting>PnYnMnDTnHnMnS</programlisting>
    <para>
      Parts of the duration which are 0 are optional. For example:
    </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>P10Y (10 years)</listitem>
      <listitem>PT30S (30 seconds)</listitem>
      <listitem>P14DT12H10M (14 days, 12 hours, 10 minutes)</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>
</section>